<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1585,1885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1793,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</emphasis>
Podosirids with their slender, evenly curved, opposable pereopods, appear to be adapted to grasping substrates, such as octocoral stems. These characteristics in place with the large second gnathopods in females (and presumably males) and the large maxilliped with elongate palps and stabbing dactyli, all indicate an ambush predator.
</paragraph>
